DataElement.preferredName: Person Current Pregnancy Estimated Date of Delivery Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date on which the person is expected to deliver the baby.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Person Current Pregnancy Estimated Date of Delivery
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A human being._Occurring in or belonging to the present time._The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth._The best estimated due date is determined by: last menstrual period (LMP) if confirmed by early ultrasound or no ultrasound performed, or early ultrasound if no known LMP or the ultrasound is not consistent with LMP, or known date of fertilization (e.g. Assisted Reproductive Technology (ART), Intrauterine Insemination (IUI)). Notes: 1. Ultrasound margin of error and "early" to be defined by SMFM/ACOG/NICHD workshop. 2. Pregnancy should not be re-dated by a later ultrasound after a best obstetrical estimate of EDD has been established. (adapted from reVITALize)

Concepts.definition: Occurring in or belonging to the present time.
The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth.

The best estimated due date is determined by: last menstrual period (LMP) if confirmed by early ultrasound or no ultrasound performed, or early ultrasound if no known LMP or the ultrasound is not consistent with LMP, or known date of fertilization (e.g. Assisted Reproductive Technology (ART), Intrauterine Insemination (IUI)). Notes: 1. Ultrasound margin of error and "early" to be defined by SMFM/ACOG/NICHD workshop. 2. Pregnancy should not be re-dated by a later ultrasound after a best obstetrical estimate of EDD has been established. (adapted from reVITALize)
